cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.NA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the analysis of estimation error in large linear systems, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the performance of the posterior mean estimator (PME), which is a common tool in machine learning. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper deals with the analysis of estimation error in the presence of additive white Gaussian noise (AWGN), which is a common topic in signal processing. 
4. cs.MM (Mathematical Methods) - The paper uses the decoupling principle, which is a mathematical tool, to link scalar channels to large linear system analyses. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper provides closed form approximations for the excess mean square error (EMSE), which can be useful in numerical analysis.
